<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-09T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-09T06:00:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/45: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-09T14:00:00+03:00">February 9, 1937—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>40. Please see last paragraph of my 690, December 22, 3 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d539fn12"><ref target="frus1936v03#pg_327"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 327</ref>.</note> Within
                                the past few days the Italian authorities have again been making
                                active preparations to take over the mission property. I have
                                advised the mission to present to the authorities a statement as to
                                the value of all its movable and immovable properties together with
                                a complete inventory.</p>
                            <p>Has the Department any instructions beyond those contained in: its
                                398, December 8, 5 p.m.?<note n="13" xml:id="d539fn13"><ref target="frus1936v03#pg_325"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p.
                                        325</ref>.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>